name: Boson string
description: It is the first and simplest form of string theory. It traditionally requires 26 dimensions to conform to physical rules and assumptions (such as Lawrence symmetry). Unfortunately, there is a tachyon (a particle that travels faster than light) in the spectrum of its particles, so it cannot be a model of nature. It also follows Bose's statistics (as opposed to Fermi in [statistical mechanics]) so it naturally cannot describe particles such as electrons. Of course, this theory succeeds in describing field particles such as gravitons and photons.
